field.value:
Routing seems to fail when you are routing to an action on a controller that exists within an area. The url produced by the routing module has the correct area/controller/action.rails fragment at the end, but it is prefixed by a fragment of the url used in the route. E.g. 

/foo/bar/3

for controller:

[ControllerDetails(Area = "Zoo")
public class BeepController : Controller {
    public void Parp(int jobby) {
    }
}

results in /foo/bar/Zoo/Beep/Parp.rails?jobby=3

The patch amends the getmrpath function in the routing module to prepend a "~/" to the start of the rewritten url. This forces the rewritten url to:

/Zoo/Beep/Parp.rails?jobby=3

as expected.
